1794\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ppp1665703531653.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ppp1665703531653.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ppp1665703531653.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ppp1665703531653\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                       \n Settings: Tracing\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__p_d175805e1_d175806e1_d175807e1\">The location where messages are displayed is determined by the settings in the Message Frame tab.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__p_d175808e1_d175809e1_d175810e1\">ProcScript error numbers -59, -65, -1109, -1121, -1122, and -1123 are always logged regardless of the tracing options that are set.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__section_xp4_hqh_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d270856e61\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__ul_m24_3qh_tcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53579e1_d53580e1_d53581e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Trace Print Level</span>—the type of\n          ProcScript-related information to be displayed <ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__ul_n24_3qh_tcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53582e1_d53583e1_d53584e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Validation</span>—steps in the\n              Uniface validation processes. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53585e1_d53586e1_d53587e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Triggers</span>— triggers that\n              are activated and exited. Triggers are identified by their name and the name of their\n              associated component, entity, or field. <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACT</code> indicates that the\n              trigger is activated, <code class=\"ph codeph\">END</code> that it is exited. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53588e1_d53589e1_d53590e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Transient ProcScript\n                errors</span>—<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> and\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span> information for ProcScript errors that do not\n              change the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>; for example, when an expression\n              contains a function that fails. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53591e1_d53592e1_d53593e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">ProcScript\n                errors</span>—<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> and\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span> information for each ProcScript error in which\n              the execution of the ProcScript statement fails. These types of ProcScript errors set\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> to a negative number. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53594e1_d53595e1_d53596e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Activate\n                errors</span>—<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> and\n                <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span> information for the activate-related ProcScript\n              errors: <code class=\"ph codeph\">-50</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">-51</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">-58</code>. </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__li_d53597e1_d53598e1_d53599e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">ProcScript tracing</span>—all\n          ProcScript statements that are executed </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppp1665703531653__p_d175814e1_d175815e1_d175816e1\">You can more easily view the context of ProcScript\n        errors by choosing View &gt;<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Error Context</span>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ibc1665703531301.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: I/O Print</a><p>Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yno1665703531917.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Triggers</a><p>Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uha1665703532184.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Errors</a><p>Set a specific ProcScript error value ($procerror) as a breakpoint.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sev1665703532366.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Settings: Message Frame</a><p>Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled, and whether application messages are sent to the application's message frame or to the application's transcript window.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ezw1665703530124.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Error Context</a><p>Displays the contents of $procerrorcontext whenever a ProcScript error occurs ($procerror&lt; 0).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gkd1665702624564.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Return Values, Status Values, and ProcScript Errors</a><p>ProcScript modules return a numeric status value in $status. This module may contain the value given as an argument to the return or exit statement, a value that indicates successful completion of a command or module, or a negative number that reflects an error.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pop1665702622413.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>&lt;$triggerAbbr&gt;</a><p>The trigger name abbreviation.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8421794\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8421794\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Settings: Tracing Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Settings: Tracing Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window. The location where messages are displayed is determined by the settings in the Message Frame tab. ProcScript error numbers -59, -65, -1109, -1121, -1122, and -1123 are always logged regardless of the tracing options that are set. Fields Trace Print Level —the type of ProcScript-related information to be displayed Validation —steps in the Uniface validation processes. Triggers — triggers that are activated and exited. Triggers are identified by their name and the name of their associated component, entity, or field. ACT indicates that the trigger is activated, END that it is exited. Transient ProcScript errors — $procerror and $procerrorcontext information for ProcScript errors that do not change the value of $status ; for example, when an expression contains a function that fails. ProcScript errors — $procerror and $procerrorcontext information for each ProcScript error in which the execution of the ProcScript statement fails. These types of ProcScript errors set $status to a negative number. Activate errors — $procerror and $procerrorcontext information for the activate-related ProcScript errors: -50 , -51 , and -58 . ProcScript tracing —all ProcScript statements that are executed You can more easily view the context of ProcScript errors by choosing View > Error Context . Related Links Settings: I/O Print Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window. Settings: Triggers Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints. Settings: Errors Set a specific ProcScript error value ($procerror) as a breakpoint. Settings: Message Frame Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled, and whether application messages are sent to the application's message frame or to the application's transcript window. Error Context Displays the contents of $procerrorcontext whenever a ProcScript error occurs ($procerror< 0). Return Values, Status Values, and ProcScript Errors ProcScript modules return a numeric status value in $status. This module may contain the value given as an argument to the return or exit statement, a value that indicates successful completion of a command or module, or a negative number that reflects an error. <$triggerAbbr> The trigger name abbreviation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}